Tottenham boss, Jose Mourinho has warned defender, Serge Aurier over mocking his previous managers. The Portuguese has won three games out of four for Tottenham in the Premier League since taking over. The Ivory Coast international has been caught up in controversy in the past, over comments made on social media about ex-boss Laurent Blanc during his time at PSG. The former PSG star was suspended by the club over the altercation, after making homophobic slurs towards Blanc via a video message, as well as to several teammates, including Zlatan Ibrahimovic. Foot Mercato quoted Mourinho as saying about Aurier, “I am not laughing. If you think that you can mock me on social media like you’ve done to some of your former managers in the past, you are mistaken.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.